    • generateConstructors

      private String generateConstructors(Class<?> token) throws info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException
      Method for generating all non-private constructors

      Generates non-private constructors with Class.getDeclaredConstructors() and generateConstructor(Constructor, Class), separating them with new line. If token is interface, than returns empty string

      token - super class or interface for future generated class
      Returns:
      code for all non-private constructors of class

      token - super class
      Returns:
      generated code for provided constructor and token

    • generateExecutableHeader

      private String generateExecutableHeader(Executable executable, String name)
      Method for generating headers for methods/constructors

      Generates string "public name (params with types) throws Exception1, Exception2, ..." with generateArguments(Executable, boolean) and generateExceptions(Executable)

      Parameters:
      executable - method or constructor
      name - string with return type and name of method for methods (e.g. "int main") or name of constructor for constructors (e.g. "Constructor")
      Returns:
      generated code for header of provided executable

    • generateArguments

      private String generateArguments(Executable executable, boolean withTypes)
      Method for generating arguments for class or method

      Generates string "type1 name_of_arg1, type2 name_of_arg2 ..." if withTypes is true (used in generateExecutableHeader(Executable, String)) and "name_of_arg1, name_of_arg2 ..." if it's false (used in generateConstructor(Constructor, Class) )

      Parameters:
      executable - class or method
      withTypes - true if it's needed types before name of arguments: "int a", false: "a"
      Returns:
      generated code of arguments for provided executable

    • generateExceptions

      private String generateExceptions(Executable executable)
      Method for generating exceptions for constructors or methods

      Obtains exceptions with Executable.getExceptionTypes(). Generate string "throws Exception1, Exception2, ..." or empty string if array with exceptions is empty

      Parameters:
      executable - constructor or method
      Returns:
      code with information about exceptions to provided executable

    • generateMethods

      private String generateMethods(Class<?> token)
      Method for generating methods of the class

      Finds all abstract methods in inheritance tree with findMethodsThroughTree(Class), than filter all non-final methods in parent (token), than generates methods with generateMethod(Method)

      Parameters:
      token - super class or interface
      Returns:
      all methods that extends abstract methods of provided token

    • generateMethod

      private String generateMethod(Method method)
      Method for generating code for method

      Generates code for method with generateExecutableHeader(Executable, String) in body will be string "return default_value" which obtained by getDefaultType(Class)

      Parameters:
      method - method for what we should generate code
      Returns:
      generated code for provided method

    • getDefaultType

      private String getDefaultType(Class<?> type)
      Method for generating default value of type

      Generates

      • "null" for Object
      • "true" for boolean
      • empty string for void
      • "0" for primitive types
      Parameters:
      type - type for generating default value
      Returns:
      default value of provided type

    • getMyMethods

      private static Map<MyMethod,Method> getMyMethods(Method[] methods)
      Method for wrapping array of Method to array of MyMethod

      Returns Map with key of MyMethod and value Method. Methods are abstract or final. If there are more than one method with equal wrappers than for value of map will be choosen with more narrow return type with minByReturnType

      Parameters:
      methods - array of Method
      Returns:
      Map with key of wrapper and value Method
      See Also:
      • MyMethod

      Parameters:
      from - first map
      to - second map with result of merging

    • findMethodsThroughTree

      private Map<MyMethod,Method> findMethodsThroughTree(Class<?> token)
      Method for finding all distinct abstract and final methods of inheritance tree

      Gets all methods of this token and its super class with Class.getDeclaredMethods(), Class.getMethods() and recursion. Then wraps them with getMyMethods(Method[]) and merge maps with mergeMaps(Map, Map)

      Parameters:
      token - super class or interface
      Returns:
      Collections.emptyMap() if token == null or Map from MyMethod to Method

    • implementJar

      public void implementJar(Class<?> token, Path jarFile) throws info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException
      Method for implementing jar file

      Implements provided token. Creates temporary directory, where .class files will be stored. Compiles classes with compileClass(Path, Class) and creates manifest for jar with createManifest(Class, Path, Path). Finally cleans temporary directory with clean(Path)

      Specified by:
      implementJar in interface info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.JarImpler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      jarFile - target .jar file.
      Throws:
      info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException - if isValid(Class) returns false or IOException occurred while creating temporary directory
